              "value": true
            },
            {
              "path": "chapter1.court_outcome",
              "value": "strong"
            }
          ],
          "result_text": "The bench grants the motion to set aside under KPC Article 135-bis § 2. Before issuing the order the judge pauses for half a beat — long enough that the bailiff looks up — and notes for the record that the four elements of the defect appear in the file in the form Article 135-bis § 2 contemplates, which the bench is not always able to say. The remedy is, of course, modest: a rehearing on the merits, scheduled in the ordinary course, costs against the petitioner. The client is restored to the proceeding. The order goes no further than that. It does not need to."
